Title: Total assets
Definition: The sum of all assets owned by the institution including cash, loans, securities, bank premises and other assets. This total does not include off-balance-sheet accounts.

Title: Average assets, quarterly
Definition: The two period average of the total assets shown on the balance sheet.  The calculation uses this quarter's and last quarter's values. An example calculation for September would be (June assets + September assets) / 2. The denominator for quarterly income as a percent of average assets.

Title: Average total assets
Definition: Year-to-date average of the total assets represented on the balance sheet. Used as the denominator for year-to-date income as a percent of average assets. The number of quarterly values used in the calculation depends on the date of the data. year-to-date averages: march reporting period - (december assets + march assets) / 2 june reporting period - (december assets + march assets + june assets) / 3 September reporting period - (December assets + March assets + June assets + September assets) / 4 December reporting period - (Previous December assets + March assets + June assets + September assets + December assets) / 5 Quarterly averages: All reporting periods – (Previous quarter assets + current quarter assets) / 2

Title: Average total assets
Definition: Year-to-date average of the total assets represented on the balance sheet. Used as the denominator for year-to-date income as a percent of average assets. The number of quarterly values used in the calculation depends on the date of the data. year-to-date averages: march reporting period - (december assets + march assets) / 2 june reporting period - (december assets + march assets + june assets) / 3 September reporting period - (December assets + March assets + June assets + September assets) / 4 December reporting period - (Previous December assets + March assets + June assets + September assets + December assets) / 5 Quarterly averages: All reporting periods – (Previous quarter assets + current quarter assets) / 2

Title: Total assets in foreign offices
Definition: The sum of all assets held in foreign offices owned by the institution including cash, loans, securities, bank premises and other assets.  This total does not include off-balance-sheet accounts.  Available for Call Reporters only.
ref_file: Total Assets and Liabilities in Foreign Offices

Title: Long-term assets (5+ years)
Definition: Loans and debt securities with remaining maturities or repricing intervals of over five years.   This item is not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Assets per employee ($millions)
Definition: Total assets in millions of dollars as a percent of the number of full-time equivalent employees.

Title: Adjusted average assets for leverage capital purposes
Definition:
As of March 2015, total average assets for leverage capital purposes according to the amended Market Risk Capital Rule. (see: FDIC Financial Institutions Letter FIL-24-1012 )

Advanced approaches institutions begin reporting a new calculation for this item beginning March 31, 2014 on schedule RC-R Part I.B.

All institutions began the new schedule RC-R Part I and Part II as of March 31, 2015.


Prior to the new RC-R requirements, average assets-adjusted based on the risk-based capital definitions for prompt corrective action (PCA) and includes:

Call Reporters:Average assets (from schedule RC-K) - disallowed intangible assets - unrealized loss on equity securities - unrealized holding gains or losses on available-for-sale securities according to FASB 115 - adjustments for financial subsidiaries (Beginning in March 2001)

Thrift Financial Reporters (before March 2012): Adjusted tangible assets (from schedule CCR)- unrealized holding gains or losses on available-for-sale securities adjusted according to FASB 115

Title: Bank Charter Class
Definition: A classification code assigned by the FDIC based on the institution's charter type (commercial bank or savings institution), charter agent (state or federal), Federal Reserve membership status (Fed member, Fed nonmember)and its primary federal regulator (state chartered institutions are subject to both federal and state supervision). n = commercial bank, national (federal) charter and fed member, supervised by the office of the comptroller of the currency (occ) sm = commercial or savings bank, state charter and fed member, supervised by the federal reserve (frb) nm = commercial bank, state charter and fed nonmember, supervised by the FDIC or OCC SB = savings banks, state charter, supervised by the FDIC SA = As of July 21, 2011, FDIC supervised state chartered thrifts and OCC supervised federally chartered thrifts. Prior to that date, state or federally chartered savings associations supervised by the Office of Thrift Supervision (OTS). OI = insured U.S. branch of a foreign chartered institution (IBA)

Title: Bank premises and fixed assets
Definition: Bank premises, furniture and fixtures, equipment and other assets representing bank premises (including capitalized leases) owned by the institution.

Title: Brokered deposits
Definition: Total brokered deposits held in domestic offices. Brokered deposits represent funds which the reporting bank obtains, directly orindirectly, by or through any deposit broker for deposit into one or more deposit accounts. Thus, brokered deposits include both those in which the entire beneficial interest in a given bank deposit account or instrument is held by a single depositor and those in which the deposit broker sells participations in a given bank deposit account or instrument to one or more investors.Fully insured brokered deposits are brokered deposits that are issued in denominations of $100,000

Title: Fully insured brokered deposits
Definition: Brokered deposits held in domestic offices issued in denominations of less than $100,000, or in denominations of $100,000 or more and participated out by the broker in shares of less than $100,000note: although standard fdic insurance coverage was temporarily raised from $100,000 to $250,000 in october 2008, institutions are required to report this item based on the $100,000 coverage limit through December 2009.

Title: The type of financial report filed to the regulators
Definition:
The type of financial report filed by an institution to the regulators.

Thrift Financial Report Filers:

100 - Savings institution Thrift Financial Report or TFR filer (3/1984 - 12/2011)

FFIEC CALL Report Filers:

002 – International Banking Act Institution (6/1980-present)

031 – Banks with domestic and foreign offices (3/1984 -present)

032 - Banks with domestic offices only and total assetsof $300 million or more ( 3/1984 - 12/2000)

033 - Banks with domestic offices only and total assetsof over $100 million but less than $300 million (3/1984 - 12/2000)

034 - Banks with domestic offices only and total assetsless than $100 million (3/1984 - 12/2000)

041 - Banks with domestic offices only (3/2001 - present)

051 - Banks with domestic offices only and total assets less than $1 billion. (3/2017 - present)

For further information on FFIEC Call Reports , click here.

For further information on Thrift Financial Reports, click here.

Title: FDIC Community Banks
Definition: FDIC Community banks are identified based on criteria defined in the fdic community banking study. using detailed balance sheet and geographic data, the study defines community banks primarily in terms of their traditional relationship banking and limited geographic scope of operations. Summary of FDIC Research Definition of Community Banking Organizations Community banks are designated at the level of the banking. (All charters under designated holding companies are considered community banking charters.) Exclude: Any organization with:    - No loans or no core deposits    - Foreign Assets ≥10% of total assets    - More than 50% of assets in certain specialty banks, including: credit card specialists consumer nonbank banks1 industrial loan companies trust companies bankers' banks Include: All remaining banking organizations with:    - Total assets 2    - Total assets ≥indexed size threshold, where: Loan to assets > 33% Core deposits to assets > 50% More than 1 office but no more than the indexed maximum number of offices.3 Number of large MSAs with offices ≤2 Number of states with offices ≤3 No single office with deposits > indexed maximum branch deposit size.4 1 Consumer nonbank banks are financial institutions with limited charters that can make commercial loans or take deposits, but not both. 2 Asset size threshold indexed to equal $250 million in 1985 and $1 billion in 2010. 3 Maximum number of offices indexed to equal 40 in 1985 and 75 in 2010. 4 Maximum branch deposit size indexed to equal $1.25 billion in 1985 and $5 billion in 2010.

Title: Time deposits of $100,000 or more: 1 to 3 years
Definition: Domestic time deposits of $100,000 or more that are either fixed rate instruments with remaining maturities of one through three years or floating rate instruments subject to repricing less often than yearly, but more often than once every three years. This item is not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Time deposits of < $100,000: 1 - 3 years
Definition: Domestic time deposits of less than $100,000, plus all open-account time deposits that are either fixed rate instruments with remaining maturities of one through three years or floating rate instruments subject to repricing less often than yearly, but more often than once every three years.  This item is not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Time deposits of $100,000 or more:3 months or less
Definition: Domestic time deposits of $100,000 or more that are either fixed rate instruments with remaining maturities of 3 months or less or floating rate instruments subject to repricing on a quarterly or more frequent basis.  This item is not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Time deposits of < $100,000: 3 months or less
Definition: Domestic time deposits of less than $100,000, plus all open-account time deposits that are either fixed rate instruments with remaining maturities of 3 months or less or floating rate instruments subject to repricing on a quarterly or more frequent basis.   This item is not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Time deposits of $100,000 or more: 3 to 12 months
Definition: Domestic time deposits of $100,000 or more that are either fixed rate instruments with remaining maturities of more than 3 months, but less than one year or floating rate instruments subject to repricing less often than quarterly, but more often than yearly. This item is not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Time deposits of < $100,000: 3 - 12  months
Definition: Domestic time deposits of less than $100,000, plus all open-account time deposits that are either fixed rate instruments with remaining maturities of more than 3 months, but less than one year or floating rate instruments subject to repricing less often than quarterly, but more often than yearly.   This item is not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Time deposits of $100,000 or more: 3 or more years
Definition: Domestic time deposits of $100,000 or more that are either fixed rate instruments with remaining maturities of more than 3 years or floating rate instruments subject to repricing every three years or more.   This item is not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Time deposits of < $100,000: 3 or more years
Definition: Domestic time deposits of less than $100,000, plus all open-account time deposits that are either fixed rate instruments with remaining maturities of more than 3 years or floating rate instruments subject to repricing every three years or more.   This item is not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: FDIC Certificate #
Definition: FDIC Certificate number - A unique NUMBER assigned by the FDIC used to identify institutions and for the issuance of insurance certificates.

Title: Cash & Balances due from depository institutions
Definition: Total cash and balances due from depository institutions including both interest-bearing and noninterest-bearing balances.

Title: Cash & Balances due from depository institutions
Definition: Total cash and balances due from depository institutions including both interest-bearing and noninterest-bearing balances.

Title: Cash and due from depository institutions
Definition: Total cash and balances due from depository institutions held in foreign offices, including both interest-bearing and noninterest-bearing balances.
ref_file: Total Assets and Liabilities in Foreign Offices

Title: Interest-bearing balances
Definition: Savings or time balances, including certificates of deposit, that are due from other depository institutions. Does not include certificates of deposit held in trading accounts.

Title: Total noninterest-bearing balances
Definition: The total noninterest-bearing cash (currency and coin) and balances due from depository institutions.

Title: Cash items in process of collection
Definition: Cash items in process of collection, including unposted debits and currency and coin.  Beginning in 2001, this item is not reported by FFIEC Call filers with less than $300 million in  total assets. Prior to 2001, this item also includes balances due from federal reserve banks for filers with total assets of less than $100 million.  It also includes noninterest-earning deposits for TFR Reporters.

Title: Currency and coin in domestic offices
Definition: Currency and coin held in domestic offices.

Title: Balances due from FRB
Definition: The total cash balances due from Federal Reserve Banks as shown by the reporting bank's books.  This amount includes reserves and other balances. Beginning in 2001, this item is not reported by FFIEC Call filers with total assets of less than $300 million. Prior to 2001, this item was reported in the 'Cash and balances due' categories for FFIEC Call Report filers with total assets of less than $100 million.   This item is not filed by TFR Reporters.

Title: Collection in domestic offices
Definition: Cash items in the process of collection and unposted debits (held in domestic offices) which are immediately payable upon presentation.  Beginning in 2001, this item is not reported by FFIEC Call filers with total assets of less than $300 million. Prior to 2001, this item also includes balances due from federal reserve banks for filers with total assets of less than $100 million.   This item is not filed by TFR Reporters.

Title: Balances due from foreign banks
Definition: Cash balances due from banks in foreign countries and foreign central banks. Beginning in 2001, this item is not reported by FFIEC Call filers with total assets of less than $300 million.    This item is not filed by TFR Reporters.

Title: Foreign branches of U.S. banks
Definition: Cash balances due from foreign branches of other U.S. banks. Beginning in 2001, this item is not reported by FFIEC Call filers with total assets of less than $300 million.    This item is not filed by TFR Reporters.

Title: Balances due from depository institutions in U.S.
Definition: Cash balances due from depository institutions in U.S. include all interest-bearing and noninterest-bearing balances whether in the form of demand, savings or time balances, including certificates of deposit but excluding certificates of deposit held for trading. Beginning in 2001, this item is not reported by FFIEC Call filers with total assets of less than $300 million.

Title: U.S. branches of foreign banks
Definition: Cash balances due from U.S. branches and agencies of foreign banks (including their International Banking Facilities) which is comprised of all interest-bearing and noninterest-bearing balances whether in the form of demand, savings or time balances, including certificates of deposit not held for trading. Beginning in 2001, this item is not reported by FFIEC Call filers with total assets of less than $300 million.    This item is not filed by TFR Reporters.

Title: City, State, Zip
Definition: City-- City in which an institution's headquarters is physically located. State -- State in which an institution's headquarters is physically located. County -- The name of the county where the institution is physically located. ZIP -- The first five digits of the full postal zip code representing physical location of the institution.

Title: View Custom Report Selections
Definition: The 'View Custom Report Selections/View Custom Report Selections for Download' screen displays if: data items were selected when creating a custom report you selected a report to download from the confirmation page Review and confirm the data items that were selected in the  creation of the custom report or by selecting a report  to download from the confirmation page.  Then press: 			  Add More - to select additional data items 	 Next - to confirm the selections and create the custom report or continue with the download

Title: View Custom Report Selections
Definition: The 'View Custom Report Selections/View Custom Report Selections for Download' screen displays if: data items were selected when creating a custom report you selected a report to download from the confirmation page Review and confirm the data items that were selected in the  creation of the custom report or by selecting a report  to download from the confirmation page.  Then press: 			  Add More - to select additional data items 	 Next - to confirm the selections and create the custom report or continue with the download

Title: Confirmation Reports
Definition: The Confirmation Report verifies the SDI database to ensure that the column selections are valid.  Invalid selections will be displayed on this report. For example, if a custom peer group is created for a given report date and then the report date is changed, the confirmation process determines whether all of the peers are valid for the modified report date. Any group that is not valid will be highlighted and will be accompanied by a message stating that the invalid peers are not available for the reporting period.   From the Confirmation Report, the user can:  Modify Report Dates 	 Modify  how income is calculated  		 year-to-date basis 			 quarterly basis 		 	 	 Make a report selection and 		 View 		 Download 		  	 Review column selections      Selecting 'Download' from the confirmation page creates a comma separated value (.CSV) file consisting solely of selected data items. Each data item from any of the SDI's  twenty-four reports can be selected.  (Note:  this download feature is based on the user's column selections and can return a maximum of two hundred records. Larger downloads can be accomplished by selecting the 'SDI Map, Definitions, and Data Download' tab from the main SDI menu.    To download from the confirmation page:

Title: Retail deposits
Definition:
The core deposit definition was changed in March 2011.
Core deposits held in domestic offices now includes:total domestic office deposits minus
(1) time deposits of more than $250,000 held indomestic offices
(2) brokered deposits of $250,000 or less held indomestic offices.

Prior to the March 2010, core deposits were calculated as follows:
Total domestic office deposits minus
(1) time deposits of $100,000 or moreheld in domestic offices.

Title: County
Definition: County where the institution is physically located (abbreviated if the county name exceeds 16 characters).

Title: Loans to finance agricultural production and other loans to farmers
Definition: Total recoveries of loans to finance agricultural production and other loans to farmers that have been credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.  This item is not available for TFR Reporters

Title: Loans to finance agricultural production and other loans to farmers
Definition: Total recoveries of loans to finance agricultural production and other loans to farmers that have been credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.  This item is reported only by institutions with assets of $300 million or less.  This item is not available for TFR Reporters

Title: Auto Loans - Recoveries
Definition: Recoveries of loans to individuals for household, family and other personal expenditures:automobile loans credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses. Quarterly Variable: CRAUTOQ

Title: Commercial and industrial loans
Definition: Total recoveries of commercial and industrial loans that have been credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.  Note: For banks with assets of less than $300 million, this item includes all other loans (loans to depository institutions, agricultural loans, etc.).

Title: Loans to individuals
Definition: Total recoveries of loans to individuals for household, family, and other personal expenditures that have been credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Title: Other Consumer Loan Recoveries
Definition: Recoveries of loans to individuals for household, family, and other personal expenditures: all other loans credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses.  Note: Beginning March 2011, excludes automobile loans. Beginning March 2001, includes recoveries of revolving credit plans other than credit cards. Quarterly Variable: CRCONOTQ

Title: Credit card loan recoveries
Definition: Total recoveries of credit cards and related plans to individuals for household, family, and other personal expenditures that have been credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution. note: 1) prior to march 2001, included recoveries of related revolving credit plans other than credit cards.

Title: Loans to depository institutions
Definition: Total recoveries of loans to depository institutions and acceptances of other banks that have been credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.  This item is not available for TFR Reporters

Title: To foreign banks
Definition: Total recoveries of loans to foreign depository institutions and acceptances of other banks that have been credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.  This information is not available on a quarterly basis.

Title: Loans to foreign governments and official institutions
Definition: Total recoveries of loans to foreign governments and official institutions that have been credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.  This item is not available for TFR Reporters

Title: Total recoveries
Definition: The total amount of recoveries of loans and lease financing receivables credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Title: Lease financing receivables
Definition: Total recoveries of lease financing receivables that have been credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.  This item is not available for TFR Reporters

Title: Other loans
Definition: Recoveries of all other loans that have been credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.  This item is not available for TFR Reporters

Title: Loans secured by real estate, total
Definition: The total amount of recoveries of loans secured by real estate credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Title: Secured by farmland
Definition: Total recoveries of loans secured by farmland (which are held in domestic offices) that have been charged-off and credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Title: 1-4 family residential construction loan recoveries
Definition: Recovered 1-4 family residential construction loans (data available as of March 2007)

Title: Other construction loans and all land development and other land loan recoveries
Definition: Recovered other construction loans and all land development and other land loans. (Data available as of March 2007)

Title: Construction and land development
Definition: Total recoveries of real estate loans (which are held in domestic offices) for construction and land development purposes that have been credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Title: Real estate loans in foreign offices
Definition: The total amount of charged-off loans secured by real estate and held in foreign offices of the institution.

Title: Home equity lines of credit - total recoveries
Definition: Total recoveries of revolving open-end loans secured by 1-4 family residential properties and extended under lines of credit (which are held in domestic offices) that have been credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Title: Secured by multifamily residential properties
Definition: Total recoveries of multifamily (5 or more) residential properties (which are held in domestic offices) that have been credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Title: Secured by nonfarm nonresidential properties
Definition: Total recoveries of nonfarm nonresidential properties (which are held in domestic offices) that have been credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Title: Secured by other nonfarm nonresidential property - recoveries
Definition: Recovered loans secured by other nonfarm nonresidential properties. Data available as of March 2007. This item was not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Secured by owner-occupied nonfarm nonresidential property - recoveries
Definition: Recovered loans secured by owner-occupied nonfarm nonresidential properties. Data available as of March 2007. This item was not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: To non-U.S. addressees
Definition: The total amount of recoveries of loans secured by real estate (whose addresses are not within the U.S.) credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.  This information is not available on a quarterly basis.

Title: Secured by 1-4 family residential properties - total recoveries
Definition: Total recoveries of loans secured by 1-4 family residential properties (which are held in domestic offices) that have been credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Title: Secured by 1-4 family residential properties - total recoveries
Definition: Total recoveries of loans secured by 1-4 family residential properties (which are held in domestic offices) that have been credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Title: Loans secured by 1-4 family junior liens – total recoveries
Definition:
Total recoveries of closed-end loans secured by junior liens 1-4 family residential properties (which are held in domestic offices) that have been credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Prior to 2004, this item is not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Loans secured by 1-4 family senior liens – total recoveries
Definition:
Total recoveries of closed-end loans secured by first liens 1-4 family residential properties (which are held in domestic offices) that have been credited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Prior to 2004, this item is not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Bank is beneficiary
Definition: Notional amount of credit derivatives on which the reporting institution has obtained a guarantee against credit losses from other parties.  Credit derivatives are off-balance sheet arrangements that allow one party (the beneficiary) to transfer the credit risk of an asset to another party (the guarantor).

Title: Bank is guarantor
Definition: Notional amount of credit derivatives on which the institution has extended credit protection to another party.  Credit derivatives are off-balance sheet arrangements that allow one party (the beneficiary) to transfer the credit risk of an asset to another party (the guarantor).

Title: Custom Peer Groups
Definition: Custom Peer Group - create custom groups of FDIC-insured institutions, 			bank holding companies, or combinations of both (up to 50 institutions) 			and then retrieve financial reports on the groups created. There are three 			primary methods for creating a custom peer group:  		 If known, enter the 				 				FDIC Certificate numbers by selecting 'Enter IDs manually.' Use the FDIC 				Certificate numbers in the appropriate area on the data form. (Note: all 				FDIC-insured institutions have an assigned Certificate number.)  			 If known, enter the  				 				OTS Docket number by selecting 'Enter IDs manually.'  Use the OTS Docket 				numbers in the appropriate area on the data form. (Note: Only those financial 				institutions that are regulated by the Office of Thrift Supervision have an 				assigned OTS Docket number.  			 Select 'Create a Peer Group' and use the 'Find' feature to select the 				institutions or bank holding companies to be included in the custom peer group. 				The 'Find' feature allows one or more criteria to be entered when locating 				FDIC-insured institutions. {mention about the add more feature? Please see 				help Selections for column n.} 	  		  	Additionally, custom peer groups can be saved and then retrieved for later use. 	Please see the help on  	Peer Groups for more details. If a group containing more 	than 50 entities is requested, check to see if a Standard Peer Group is available.

Title: Custom Report Selections
Definition: Selecting the 'Custom Reports' choice from the Report Selection drop-down menu creates a report consisting solely of selected data items. Each data item from any of the twenty-four reports within the SDI system can be selected.  To create a custom report:

Title: Demand deposits
Definition: Total demand deposits included in transaction accounts held in domestic offices. prior to 2004, this item is not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Total deposits
Definition: The sum of all deposits including demand deposits, money market deposits, other savings deposits, time deposits and deposits in foreign offices.

Title: Total deposits
Definition: The sum of all deposits including demand deposits, money market deposits, other savings deposits, time deposits and deposits in foreign offices.

Title: Total domestic deposits to total assets
Definition: Total domestic office deposits as a percent of total assets.

Title: Deposits held in domestic offices
Definition: The sum of all domestic office deposits, including demand deposits, money market deposits, other savings deposits and time deposits.

Title: Deposits held in domestic offices
Definition: The sum of all domestic office deposits, including demand deposits, money market deposits, other savings deposits and time deposits.

Title: Banks in foreign countries
Definition: Deposits of foreign banks (including U.S. branches and agencies of foreign banks) held in foreign offices.

Title: Banks in foreign countries
Definition: Deposits of foreign banks (including U.S. branches and agencies of foreign banks) held in foreign offices.
ref_file: Total Assets and Liabilities in Foreign Offices

Title: Foreign governments and official institutions
Definition: Deposits of foreign governments and official institutions (including foreign central banks) held in foreign offices.

Title: Foreign governments and official institutions
Definition: Deposits of foreign governments and official institutions (including foreign central banks) held in foreign offices.
ref_file: Total Assets and Liabilities in Foreign Offices

Title: Deposits held in foreign offices
Definition: The sum of all foreign office deposits, including demand deposits, money market deposits, other savings deposits and time deposits.  *  This item is not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Deposits held in foreign offices
Definition: The sum of all foreign office deposits, including demand deposits, money market deposits, other savings deposits and time deposits.  *  This item is not available for TFR Reporters.
ref_file: Total Assets and Liabilities in Foreign Offices

Title: Deposits held in foreign offices
Definition: The sum of all foreign office deposits, including demand deposits, money market deposits, other savings deposits and time deposits.  *  This item is not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Interest-bearing deposits
Definition: Interest-bearing deposits (includes interest-bearing deposits in foreign offices).

Title: Interest-bearing deposits
Definition: The sum of interest-bearing time and savings deposits held in domestic offices.  This item is not available for Thrift Financial Report filers having both assets less than $300 million and risk-based capital ratios if 12 percent or more.

Title: Interest-bearing deposits
Definition: The sum of interest-bearing time and savings deposits held in foreign offices.   This item is not available for TFR Reporters.
ref_file: Total Assets and Liabilities in Foreign Offices

Title: Interest-bearing deposits
Definition: The sum of interest-bearing time and savings deposits held in foreign offices.   This item is not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Estimated insured deposits
Definition: The estimated amount of FDIC insured deposits in domestic offices and in insured branches of Puerto Rico and US territories and possessions. notes: (1) as of july 21, 2010, the standard maximum deposit insurance amount was permanently raised to $250,000. (2) Beginning December 31, 2010, through December 31, 2012, includes the unlimited insurance coverage of noninterest-bearing transaction accounts. all noninterest-bearing transaction accounts are fully insured, regardless of the balance of the account, at all FDIC-insured institutions. (3) Beginning September 2009, amounts for non-retirement accounts are reported based on the temporary increase to the standard insurance limit to $250,000. (4) Prior to September 2009, amounts for non-retirement accounts were reported based on the standard insurance limit of $100,000. (5) Beginning in 2006, retirement accounts are insured to $250,000 and reporting was phased in at different times during the year by banks, thrifts and IBAs. (6) Prior to March 2002, reported for domestic offices only. (7) This calculation uses the self-reported estimate of uninsured deposits filed by institutions that are greater than $1 billion.

Title: Individuals, partnerships and corporations
Definition: Total transaction and nontransaction accounts of individuals, partnerships and corporations (including all certified and official checks) held in foreign offices.  This item is not available for TFR reporters with assets less than $300 million and risk-based capital ratios in excess of 12 percent.

Title: Individuals, partnerships and corporations
Definition: Total transaction and nontransaction accounts of individuals, partnerships and corporations (including all certified and official checks) held in foreign offices.  This item is not available for TFR reporters with assets less than $300 million and risk-based capital ratios in excess of 12 percent.
ref_file: Total Assets and Liabilities in Foreign Offices

Title: Amount ($) deposit accounts of more than $100,000
Definition: Amount of deposit accounts of more than $100,000 held in domestic offices and in insured branches in Puerto Rico and U.S. territories and possessions note: 1.) Beginning september 2009, institutions are required to report most deposits on the $250,000 threshold levels. 2.)beginning june 2006, excludes retirement accounts for Call Reporters. 3.) Beginning September 2006, excludes retirement accounts for Insured U.S. Branches of a foreign chartered institutions (IBAs). 4.) Beginning December 2006, excludes retirement accounts for TFR Reporters.
ref_file: Deposits Based on the $100,000 Reporting Threshold

Title: Number (#) of deposit accounts more then $100,000
Definition: Number of individual deposit accounts of more than $100,000 held in domestic offices and insured U.S. branches of a foreign chartered institutions (IBAs). As of March 1991, this item is reported on a quarterly basis and is listed as memoranda only. beginning june 2006, excludes retirement accounts for call reporters and beginning september 2006, excludes retirement accounts for ibas.
ref_file: Deposits Based on the $100,000 Reporting Threshold

Title: Amount ($) of retirement deposit accounts of more than $250,000
Definition: The total amount of retirement deposit accounts (demand, savings, and time) of more than $250,000 held in domestic offices and insured branches in US territories.
ref_file: Deposits Based on the $250,000 Reporting Threshold

Title: Number (#) of retirement deposit accounts of more than $250,000
Definition: The total number of retirement deposit accounts (demand, savings, and time) with a balance on the report date of more than $250,000 held in domestic offices and insured branches in US territories.
ref_file: Deposits Based on the $250,000 Reporting Threshold

Title: Deposits obtained via list services, yet not brokered
Definition:
Estimated amount of deposits obtained through the use of deposit listing services that are not brokered.

Available as of March 2011

Title: Noninterest-bearing deposits
Definition:
The sum of total demand deposits and noninterest-bearing time and savings deposits held in domestic offices.

Prior to 2004, this item is not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Noninterest-bearing deposits
Definition: The sum of total demand deposits and noninterest-bearing time and savings deposits held in foreign offices.   This item is not available for TFR Reporters.
ref_file: Total Assets and Liabilities in Foreign Offices

Title: Noninterest-bearing deposits
Definition: The sum of total demand deposits and noninterest-bearing time and savings deposits held in foreign offices.   This item is not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Amount ($) Deposit accounts of $100,000 or less
Definition: Amount of deposit accounts of $100,000 or less held in domestic offices and in insured branches in Puerto Rico and U.S. territories and possessions beginning september 2009, institutions are required to report most deposits on the $250,000 threshold levels. beginning june 2006, excludes retirement accounts for Call Reporters. Beginning September 2006, excludes retirement accounts for Insured U.S. branches of a foreign chartered institutions (IBA). Beginning December 2006, excludes retirement accounts for TFR Reporters.
ref_file: Deposits Based on the $100,000 Reporting Threshold

Title: Number (#) of deposit accounts of $ 100,000 or less (June only for Call)
Definition: Number of deposit accounts of $ 100,000 or less held in domestic offices. This is listed as a memoranda only. beginning september 2009, institutions are required to report most deposits on the $250,000 threshold levels. Beginning June 2006, excludes retirement accounts for Call Reporters. Call Reporters provide this item only on the June Call report. TFR Reporters provide this item each quarter.
ref_file: Deposits Based on the $100,000 Reporting Threshold

Title: Amount ($) of retirement deposit accounts of $250,000 or less
Definition:
The balance of all retirement deposit accounts (demand, savings, and time) with a balance of $250,000 or less held in domestic offices and insured branches in US territories.

Notice: Insured deposit amounts or deposit thresholds reflect permanent insurance limits in effect as of the report date, not withstanding temporary increases currently in effect.
ref_file: Deposits Based on the $250,000 Reporting Threshold

Title: Number (#) of retirement deposit accounts of $250,000 or less
Definition: Total number of retirement deposit accounts (demand, savings, and time) with a balance on the report date of $250,000 or less, held in domestic offices and in insured branches in US territories. important note: for call reporters and iba filers, this item is reported only on the june call report.
ref_file: Deposits Based on the $250,000 Reporting Threshold

Title: Commercial banks and other depository institutions in U.S.
Definition: Deposits of U.S. banks (including IBFs and foreign branches of U.S. banks) and other depository institutions in the U.S that are held in foreign offices.

Title: Commercial banks and other depository institutions in U.S.
Definition: Deposits of U.S. banks (including IBFs and foreign branches of U.S. banks) and other depository institutions in the U.S that are held in foreign offices.
ref_file: Total Assets and Liabilities in Foreign Offices

Title: U.S government, states, and political subdivisions
Definition: Deposits of U.S. government, states and political subdivisions in the U.S. that are held in foreign offices.

Title: U.S government, states, and political subdivisions
Definition: Deposits of U.S. government, states and political subdivisions in the U.S. that are held in foreign offices.
ref_file: Total Assets and Liabilities in Foreign Offices

Title: Download Selections
Definition: Selecting 'Download' from the confirmation page creates a comma separated value (.CSV) file consisting solely of selected data items. Each data item from any of the SDI's  twenty-four reports can be selected.  (Note:  this download feature is based on the user's column selections and can return a maximum of two hundred records. Larger downloads can be accomplished by selecting the  'SDI Map, Definitions, and Data Download' tab from the main SDI menu.    To download from the confirmation page:

Title: Download Selection Criteria Confirmation
Definition: Download Selection Criteria Confirmation   Review and confirm the criteria used for the download.     From this page: 	 	 view the number of institutions to be included in the report and the size of the file to be downloaded. 	 review the selection criteria used for the download file 	 proceed by pressing the : 		 		 "Download" button to obtain the file 		 "Change Criteria" button to modify selection criteria 		 "Start Over" button to reset and reinitiate the entire download process 		  	 		  Continue by pressing the "Download" button. Remember to save the file with a .CSV extension and press "OK" to proceed. Do not press OK repeatedly as it will slow the processing of information.  Choose to save the file to disk and then press "OK" again.  Enter the following: 	 	 directory and path in which to save the file 	 name for the downloaded file (Reminder: The file must have a .CSV extension in order to be readable). 	   Press "Save"

Title: Download Selections
Definition: Download Selections  "Download" any data item from SDI.  Any of the SDI's data items included in its twenty-four reports can be downloaded as a comma separated variable file (.CSV). Choose from nineteen distinct search boxes to generate lists of FDIC-insured institutions for the download file. Files of sizes up to 2.5 megabytes can be downloaded. It is recommended that users file a Freedom of Information Act (FOIA) (note: hyperlink to FDIC FOIA) request to obtain information that is too large to download. (Note: this download feature is independent of the column selections used to create reports in SDI and the download capability that exists within the column selection scenario).    To download from the top menu bar:   	 Select "SDI Map, Definitions, and Data Download". 	 Select the "Data Download" button and press "Next". 	 Select the report that contains the requisite data item.   Choose from the following reports:   	 Assets and liabilities  		 		 Cash and balances due 		 Securities 		 Net loans and leases 			 			 Loans to depository institutions 			 Net loans and leases in foreign offices			 			 Maturity and repricing for loans and                  leases      			 			  		 Other real estate owned 		 Total deposits 			 			 Total deposits of less than $100,000 			 Total deposits of $100,000 or more     	 			  	 Total unused commitments 			 			 Letters of credit 			 Financial assets transferred   			 	 	 Total assets in foreign offices 	 Off-balance-sheet derivatives 	 Past due and nonaccrual assets     	   Income and expense 		 		 Total interest income 		 Total interest expense 		 Loan charge-offs 		 Foreign office income and expense 		 Changes in equity capital    		   Performance and condition ratios   		    After the report has been selected, "check" the requisite item(s)  Repeat steps 1 and 2 as necessary.  Press "Next" after all items have been selected.		  A confirmation page will appear. Press:  	 	 Add More - to select additional data items 	 Next - to confirm the selections and create the          custom report           	   A page titled "Download Selection      Criteria" will appear. One or more criteria can be entered to locate      and download financial reports for FDIC-insured institutions. The download      file is based on the information entered as the selection criteria. The      selection criteria is divided into two categories:                                               Basic 	 	 Institution Name - the entire name, or part of the name, of a specific institution may be entered to produce an Institution List of available selections.	 	 City - the city in which the financial institution's headquarters are physically located. Either the entire city name or part of the name may be entered to produce a list of choices.	 	 State - the state in which the financial institutions' headquarters are physically located. The FDIC Act defines State as any "State of the United States, the District of Columbia, and any territory of the United States, Puerto Rico, Guam, American Samoa, the Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands, the Virgin Island, and the Northern Mariana Islands."	  		Select multiple states for download by constantly holding the CTRL key while making selections.	 	 Status - an institution's status is based on the most recent demographic information, Status selections are:  		 		 Active -- Institutions that are currently open and insured by the FDIC  		 Inactive -- Institutions that are currently closed but were once insured by the FDIC  		 All -- Both active and inactive institutions 		  	 Sort by - the order in which the list of institutions will be sorted.   The default sort order of an Institution List is based on institution name. If an alternative sort order is desired, select one from the drop-down box. Available sort choices are: {Compress - Expand}	 		 		 Bank Name 		 City, State 		 FDIC Certificate Number 		 Inactive Date 		 Institution Class 		 Established Date 		 Net Income (qtr) 		 Net Income (ytd) 		 QBP Commercial Bank Region 		 State, City 		 Total Assets 		 Total Deposits 		  		  	 Information as of - The financial information date selected from the drop-down box will generate data for the period ending on that date	 	   Advanced 	 	 Specialized Categories (FAQ) - frequently asked questions which include: 		 		 Top 100 Banks and thrifts by Assets 		 Agricultural Banks 		 Banks Headquartered in US with Foreign Offices 		 Banks Directly Owned by Another Bank 		 Credit Card Institutions 		 Federally Chartered Institutions 		 Institutions with Interstate Branches 		 Mutual (Non Stock) Institutions 		 "Oakar" Institutions 		 "Sasser" Institutions 		 State Chartered Institutions 		 Stock Held Savings Institutions 		 Subchapter S Corporations 		  	 Established (After Date/Before Date) - The date on which the institution began operations. 	 Inactive Date (After Date/before Date) - The date that the institution, once insured by the FDIC, was closed. 	 Size or Performance (Greater than/Less than) - Size criteria (assets or deposits) or net income (year-to-date or quarter) may be selected from a drop-down box. A dollar amount (in millions) must also be entered in one of the two size selection boxes. Criteria will default to the minimum and maximum values if no size criteria are entered. 	 Charter Type - the legal authorization to conduct business granted to a financial institution by federal or state government. 		 		 All Charters 		 Insured Commercial Banks 		 Insured Savings Institutions 		 Insured Branches of Foreign Banks 		  	 Chartering Agency - the agency or jurisdiction responsible for issuing a charter to a FDIC-insured depository institution. 		 		 All Chartering Agencies - State and Federal 		 Comptroller of the Currency - Chartering authority for nationally (federally) chartered commercial banks 		 Office of Thrift Supervision - Chartering authority for federally chartered savings associations 		 State (includes U.S. Territories) - Chartering authority for institutions that are not chartered by the OCC or OTS 		  	 Federal Regulator - the agency primarily responsible for regulating a FDIC-insured depository institution. 		 		 All Federal Regulators 		 Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation 		 Federal Reserve Board 		 Comptroller of the Currency 		 Office of Thrift Supervision 		  	 Insurance Fund - fund to which FDIC-insured depository institutions primarily belong. 		 		 Both BIF and SAIF 		 Bank Insurance Fund (BIF)- Institutions that are primary members of the Bank Insurance Fund 		 Savings Association Insurance Fund (SAIF) - Institutions that are primary members of the Savings Association Insurance Fund 		  	 Quarterly Banking Profile Region - The Quarterly Banking Profile (QBP) Commercial Bank Region in which the institution is physically located. Select from a drop down box. Click here (note: hyperlink to QBP Region breakdown) for regional breakdown. 	  	Note: Group data by QBP Region is only available for Insured Commercial Banks and Insured Savings Institutions and NOT for All Insured Institutions, Insured Commercial Banks by asset size and Insured Savings Institutions by asset size.	 	 FDIC Field Office - The FDIC Field Office where the institution is physically located. 	     After all selection criteria has been entered the user must press "Find."  A Download Selection Criteria Confirmation screen will appear. From this screen: 	 	 view the number of institutions to be included in the report and the size of the file to be downloaded. 	 review the selection criteria used for the download file 	 proceed by pressing the : 		 		 "Download" button to obtain the file 		 "Change Criteria" button to modify selection criteria 		 "Start Over" button to reset and reinitiate the entire download process 		  	   Continue by pressing the "Download" button. Remember to save the file with a .CSV extension and press "OK" to proceed. Do not press OK multiple times as it will slow the processing of information.  Choose to save the file to disk and then press "OK" again.  Enter the following: 	 	 directory and path in which to save the file 	 name for the downloaded file (Reminder: The file must have a .CSV extension in order to be readable). 	   Press "Save".

Title: Loans to finance agricultural production and other loans to farmers
Definition: Total loans to finance agricultural production and other loans to farmers that have been charged-off and debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.  This item is not available for TFR Reporters

Title: Loans to finance agricultural production and other loans to farmers
Definition: Total loans to finance agricultural production and other loans to farmers that have been charged-off and debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.  This item is reported only by institutions with assets of $300 million or less.  This item is not available for TFR Reporters

Title: Auto Loans Charge-Offs
Definition: Charged-off loans to individuals for household, family, and other personal expenditures:  Automobile loans debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses. Quarterly variable: DRAUTOQ

Title: Commercial and industrial loans
Definition: Total commercial and industrial loans that have been charged-off and debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.  Note: For banks with assets of less than $300 million, this item includes all other loans (loans to depository institutions, agricultural loans, etc.).

Title: Loans to individuals
Definition: Total loans to individuals for household, family, and other personal expenditures that have been charged-off and debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Title: Other Consumer Loan Charge-Offs
Definition: Charged-off loans to individuals for household, family, and other personal expenditures: all other loans debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses.  Note: Prior to March  2011, excludes automobile loans.  Beginning March 2001, includes revolving creditplans other than credit cards. Quarterly Variable: DRCONOTQ

Title: Credit card loan charge offs
Definition: Total credit cards and related plans to individuals for household, family, and other personal expenditures that have been charged-off and debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution. note: 1) prior to march 2001, included charge-offs of related revolving credit plans other than credit cards.

Title: Loans to depository institutions
Definition: Total loans to depository institutions and acceptances of other banks that have been charged-off and debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.  This item is not available for TFR Reporters

Title: To foreign banks
Definition: Total loans to foreign depository institutions and acceptances of other banks that have been charged-off and debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.  This information is not available on a quarterly basis.

Title: Loans to foreign governments and official institutions
Definition: Total loans to foreign governments and official institutions that have been charged-off and debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.  This item is not available for TFR Reporters

Title: Total charge-offs
Definition: The total amount of charged-off loans and lease financing receivables debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Title: Lease financing receivables
Definition: Total lease financing receivables that have been charged-off and debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.  This item is not available for TFR Reporters

Title: Other loans
Definition: All other loans that have been charged-off and debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.  This item is not available for TFR Reporters

Title: Loans secured by real estate, total
Definition: The total amount of charged-off loans secured by real estate debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Title: Secured by farmland
Definition: Total loans secured by farmland (which are held in domestic offices) that have been charged-off and debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.  This item is not available for TFR Reporters

Title: 1-4 family residential construction loan charge offs
Definition: Charged off 1-4 family residential construction loans. (Data available as of March 2007)

Title: Other construction loans and all land development and other land loan charge off
Definition: Charged off other construction loans and all land development and other land loans. (Data available as of March 2007)

Title: Construction and land development
Definition: Total real estate loans (which are held in domestic offices) for construction and land development purposes that have charged-off and debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Title: Real estate loans in foreign offices
Definition: The total amount of charged-off loans secured by real estate and held in foreign offices of the institution.

Title: Total charge offs - home equity lines of credit
Definition: Total revolving, open-end loans secured by 1-4 family residential properties and extended under lines of credit (which are held in domestic offices) that have been charged-off and debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Title: Secured by multifamily residential properties
Definition: Total multifamily (5 or more) residential properties (which are held in domestic offices) that have been charged-off and debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Title: Secured by nonfarm nonresidential properties
Definition: Total nonfarm nonresidential properties (which are held in domestic offices) that have been charged-off and debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Title: Secured by other nonfarm nonresidential properties - charge offs
Definition: Charged off loans secured by other nonfarm nonresidential properties. Data available as of March 2007.This item was not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Secured by owner-occupied nonfarm nonresidential properties - charge offs
Definition: Charged off loans secured by owner-occupied nonfarm nonresidential properties. Data available as of March 2007.This item was not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: To non-U.S. addressees
Definition: The total amount of charged-off loans secured by real estate (whose addresses are not within the U.S.) debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution. This information is not available on a quarterly basis.

Title: Total charge-offs secured by 1-4 family residential properties
Definition: Total loans secured by 1-4 family residential properties (which are held in domestic offices) that have been charged-off and debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Title: Total charge-offs secured by 1-4 family residential properties
Definition: Total loans secured by 1-4 family residential properties (which are held in domestic offices) that have been charged-off and debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Title: Loans secured by 1-4 family junior liens – total charge-offs
Definition:
Closed-end loans secured by junior liens 1-4 family residential properties (which are held in domestic offices) that have been charged-off and debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Prior to 2004, this item is not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Loans secured by 1-4 family senior liens – total charge-offs
Definition:
Closed-end loans secured by first liens 1-4 family residential properties (which are held in domestic offices) that have been charged-off and debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses established by the institution.

Prior to 2004, this item is not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Goodwill impairment losses and amortization expense
Definition: Goodwill impairment losses and amortization expense and impairment loss for other intangible assets on a consolidated basis

Title: Contracts on other commodities and equities.
Definition: National amount of total equity derivative contracts, commodity contracts and other contracts. Not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Interest expense: Domestic office deposits
Definition: Total interest expense on deposits held in domestic offices.

Title: Interest expense: Foreign office deposits
Definition: Total interest expense on deposits held in foreign offices, Edge and agreement subsidiaries and IBFs.

Title: Interest expense: Foreign office deposits
Definition: Total interest expense on deposits held in foreign offices, Edge and agreement subsidiaries and IBFs.
ref_file: Interest income and expense in foreign offices

Title: Efficiency ratio
Definition: Noninterest expense less amortization of intangible assets as a percent of net interest income plus noninterest income. This ratio measures the proportion of net operating revenues that are absorbed by overhead expenses, so that a lower value indicates greater efficiency.

Title: Last Structure Change Effective Date
Definition: Effective Start Date of the data contained in this row.

Title: Interest expense: Federal funds purchased
Definition: Total interest expense on federal funds purchased and securities sold under agreements to repurchase in domestic offices of the bank and of its Edge and agreement subsidiaries, and in IBFs.

Title: Total interest expense
Definition: Total interest expense

Title: Total interest expense
Definition: Total interest expense

Title: Goodwill impairment losses
Definition: Goodwill impairment losses. This item is not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Amortization expense and impairment losses for other intangible losses
Definition: Amortization expense and impairment losses for other intangible assets. This item is not available for TFR Reporters.

Title: Credit loss provision to net charge-offs
Definition: Provision for possible credit and allocated transfer risk as a percent of net charge-offs. If the denominator is less than or equal to zero, then ratio is shown as 'NA.'

Title: Provision for loan and lease losses
Definition: The amount needed to make the allowance for loan and lease losses adequate to absorb expected loan and lease losses (based upon management's evaluation of the bank's current loan and lease portfolio). call reporters: prior to 2001 and after 2002, an allowance for transfer risk is also included to cover losses on international assets. Additionally, from 1997 to 2000, includes provision for credit losses on off-balance sheet credit exposures. TFR Reporters: Reflects net provision for losses on interest-bearing assets.

Title: Loan and lease loss provision to assets
Definition: The annualized provision for loans and lease losses as a percent of average total assets on a consolidated basis.

Title: Maximum Amount of Credit Exposure, Credit Enhancements Auto Loans
Definition: Auto LoansMaximum Amount Of Credit Exposure Arising From CreditEnhancements Provided By The Reporting Bank To OtherStandby Letters Of Credit, Purchase Subordinated Securities, And Other Enhancements - Auto Loans.
ref_file: Maximum Amount of Credit Exposure Retained

Title: Maximum Amount of Credit Exposure, Credit Enhancements C&I Loans
Definition: Commercial & Industrial LoansMaximum Amount Of Credit Exposure Arising From CreditEnhancements Provided By The Reporting Bank To OtherStandby Letters Of Credit, Purchase Subordinated Securities, And Other Enhancements - Commercial And Industrial Loans.
ref_file: Maximum Amount of Credit Exposure Retained

Title: Maximum Amount of Credit Exposure, Credit Enhancements Other Consumer Loans
Definition: Other Consumer LoansMaximum Amount Of Credit Exposure Arising From CreditEnhancements Provided By The Reporting Bank To OtherStandby Letters Of Credit, Purchase Subordinated Securities, And Other Enhancements - Other Consumer Loans.
ref_file: Maximum Amount of Credit Exposure Retained

Title: Maximum Amount of Credit Exp, Credit Enhncmts Credit Cards Recbls before June 18
Definition:
Credit Cards ReceivablesMaximum Amount Of Credit Exposure Arising From CreditEnhancements Provided By The Reporting Bank To OtherStandby Letters Of Credit, Purchase Subordinated Securities, And Other Enhancements - Credit Card Receivables.

This line item ends March 2018, institutions now report any of these in All Other Loans and All Leases.
ref_file: Maximum Amount of Credit Exposure Retained

Title: Maximum Amount of Credit Exposure, Credit Enhance Home Equity before June 2018
Definition:
Home Equity LinesMaximum Amount Of Credit Exposure Arising From CreditEnhancements Provided By The Reporting Bank To OtherStandby Letters Of Credit, Purchase Subordinated Securities, AndOther Enhancements - Home Equity Lines.

This line item ends March 2018, institutions now report any of these in All Other Loans and All Leases.
ref_file: Maximum Amount of Credit Exposure Retained

Title: Maximum Amount of Credit Exposure, Credit Enhancements All Other Lns. &  All Ls.
Definition: All Other Loans and All LeasesMaximum Amount Of Credit Exposure Arising From CreditEnhancements Provided By The Reporting Bank To OtherStandby Letters Of Credit, Purchase Subordinated Securities, And Other Enhancements - All Other Loans, Other Assets and Leases.Beginning June 2018 All other loans also includes home equity lines,credit card receivables, auto loans, other consumerloans and commercial and industrial loans for institutions filing a FFIEC Call Report 41 .Also beginning June 2018 All other loans also includes home equity lines and credit card receivables for institutions filing a FFIEC Call Report 31 .
ref_file: Maximum Amount of Credit Exposure Retained

Title: Maximum Amount of Credit Exposure, Credit Enhancements 1-4 Family Residential Ln
Definition: 1-4 Family Residential LoansMaximum Amount Of Credit Exposure Arising From CreditEnhancements Provided By The Reporting Bank To OtherStandby Letters Of Credit, Purchase Subordinated Securities, AndOther Enhancements - 1-4 Family Residential Loans.
ref_file: Maximum Amount of Credit Exposure Retained

Title: All other noninterest expense
Definition:
All other noninterest expense on a consolidated basis.

May include:
Data processing expenses,
Advertising and marketing expenses,
Directors’ fees,
Printing, stationery, and supplies,
Postage,
Legal fees and expenses,
FDIC deposit insurance assessments,
Expenses related to the testing and training of officers and employees,
Accounting and auditing expenses,
Consulting and advisory expenses,
Automated teller machine (ATM) and interchange expenses, and
Telecommunications expenses.

For Call Reporters prior to March 2001, it includes the amortization of intangible assets. It does not include losses on asset sales for TFR Reporters.beginning in June 1996; such gains (losses) are includednet in noninterest income.

Title: Premises and equipment expense
Definition: Expenses of bank premises and fixed assets, net of rental income. Excludes salaries and employee benefits and mortgage interest.

Title: Bank equity capital
Definition: Total bank equity capital (includes preferred and common stock, surplus and undivided profits).

Title: Bank equity capital
Definition: Total bank equity capital (includes preferred and common stock, surplus and undivided profits).

Title: Average equity
Definition: The average of total equity capital (includes preferred and common stock, surplus and undivided profits). Averages are calculated as follows: Year-to-date averages: March reporting period - (December equity + March equity) / 2 June reporting period - (December equity + March equity + June equity) / 3 September reporting period - (December equity + March equity + June equity + September equity) / 4 December reporting period - (Previous December equity + March equity + June equity + September equity + December equity) / 5 Quarterly averages: All reporting periods – (Previous quarter equity + current quarter equity) / 2

Title: Other transactions with parent holding company
Definition:
Other transactions involving the institution's parent holding company which affect equity capital directly such as capital contributions other than those for stock or dividends to the holding company in the form of property rather than cash. Institutions with total assets of less than $100 million file these data only on the December Call Report.

Prior to 2004, this item is not available for TFR reporters.

Title: Other comprehensive income
Definition: Other comprehensive income The bank’s other comprehensive income for the calendar year-to-date. Other comprehensive income includes: The change during the calendar year-to-date in net unrealized holding gains (losses) on the bank’s available-for-sale securities. The change during the calendar year-to-date in the bank’s accumulated net gains (losses) on cash flow hedges. On the FFIEC 031 only, the increase or decrease during the calendar year-to-date in the bank’s cumulative foreign currency translation adjustments and qualifying foreign currency transaction gains and losses, net of applicable income taxes, if any. The change during the calendar year-to-date in any minimum pension liability adjustment recognized in accordance with FASB Statement No. 87, Employers’ Accounting for Pensions. Prior to 2004, this item is not available for TFR Reporters

Title: Cash dividends
Definition: Cash dividends paid on common and preferred stock.

Title: Cash dividends
Definition: Cash dividends paid on common and preferred stock.

Title: Cash dividends declared on common stock
Definition: Cash dividends declared on common stock during the calendar year-to-date.  Prior to 2001, institutions with total assets of less than $100 million file these data only on the December Call Report.

Title: Cash dividends declared on common stock
Definition: Cash dividends declared on common stock during the calendar year-to-date.  Prior to 2001, institutions with total assets of less than $100 million file these data only on the December Call Report.

Title: Cash dividends declared on preferred stock
Definition: Cash dividends declared on preferred stock during the calendar year-to-date.  Prior to 2001, institutions with total assets of  less than $100 million file these data only on the December Call Report.

Title: Cash dividends declared on preferred stock
Definition: Cash dividends declared on preferred stock during the calendar year-to-date.  Prior to 2001, institutions with total assets of  less than $100 million file these data only on the December Call Report.

Title: Changes incidental to business combinations, net
Definition: Changes that occur as a result of pooling of interest, purchase acquisition, or push down accounting.  Institutions with total assets of  less than $100 million file these data only on the December Call Report.  This item is not available for TFR reporters.

Title: Equity, minor interest in consolidated subs
Definition: Non-controlling (minority) interests in consolidated subsidiaries, equity capital component. note: 1) beginning March 2009, total equity includes the non-controlling (minority) interests in consolidated subsidiaries for CALL report and TFR filers.

Title: Amended balance at previous year-end
Definition: Amended bank equity capital beginning balance of the institution at previous calendar year-end.  Institutions with total assets of less than $100 million file these data only on the December Call Report.

Title: Restatements from amended reports of income, net
Definition: The sum of all corrections, net of applicable income taxes, resulting from material accounting errors which were made in prior years' Reports of Condition and Income and not corrected by the filing of an amended report for the period in which the error was made. Also includes the cumulative effect, net of applicable income taxes, of those changes in accounting principles adopted during the calendar year-to-date reporting period that were applied retroactively and for which prior years' financial statements were restated. prior to 2004, this item is not available for tfr reporters.

Title: Common stock
Definition: Common stock issued by the institution.

Title: Sale, conversion, retirement of capital stock, net
Definition: Sale, conversion, acquisition, or retirement of capital stock, net.  Included are the sale of the institution's perpetual preferred stock or common stock; exercise of stock options, conversion of convertible debt, limited life preferred stock, or perpetual preferred stock into common stock or perpetual preferred; redemption and retirement of perpetual preferred stock or common stock; treasury stock transactions; and capital related transactions involving the institution's employee stock ownership plan.  Institutions with total assets of less than $100 million file these data only on the December Call Report.

Title: Sale, conversion, retirement of capital stock, net
Definition: Sale, conversion, acquisition, or retirement of capital stock, net.  Included are the sale of the institution's perpetual preferred stock or common stock; exercise of stock options, conversion of convertible debt, limited life preferred stock, or perpetual preferred stock into common stock or perpetual preferred; redemption and retirement of perpetual preferred stock or common stock; treasury stock transactions; and capital related transactions involving the institution's employee stock ownership plan.  Institutions with total assets of less than $100 million file these data only on the December Call Report.

Title: Net treasury stock transactions
Definition: The net treasury stock transaction on a consolidated basis. The change in the bank’s total equity capital during the calendar year to date from the acquisition (without retirement) and resale or other disposal of the bank's own perpetual preferred stock or common stock, i.e., treasury stock transactions.

Title: Perpetual preferred stock
Definition: Perpetual preferred stock is preferred stock that does not have a stated maturity date or that cannot be redeemed at the option of the holder. It includes those issues of preferred stock that automatically convert into common stock at a stated date.

Title: Surplus
Definition: That portion of an institution's capital received for shares of stock sold in excess of par value (excludes all surplus related to preferred stock).

Title: Total equity capital
Definition: Total equity capital on a consolidated basis note: 1) beginning march 2009, includes the non-controlling (minority) interests in consolidated subsidiaries for CALL report and TFR filers.

Title: Undivided profits
Definition: Undivided profits, capital reserves, net unrealized holdings gains (losses) on available-for-sale securities, other equity capital components, and accumulated gains (losses) on cash flow hedges.

Title: Equity capital to assets
Definition: Total equity capital as a percent of total assets.

Title: Earning assets
Definition: All loans and other investments that earn interest or dividend income.

Title: Average earning assets
Definition: The average of all loans and other investments that earn interest or dividends. Averages are calculated as follows: Year-to-date averages: March reporting period - (December earning assets + March earning assets) / 2 June reporting period - (December earning assets + March earning assets + June earning assets) / 3 September reporting period - (December earning assets + March earning assets + June earning assets + September earning assets) / 4 December reporting period - (Previous December earning assets + March earning assets + June earning assets + September earning assets + December earning assets) / 5 Quarterly averages: All reporting periods – (Previous quarter earning assets + current quarter earning assets) / 2

Title: Earning assets to total assets ratio
Definition: Interest earning assets as a percent of total assets.

Title: Salaries and employee benefits
Definition: Salaries and employee benefits expense.

Title: Established
Definition: After Date/Before Date - The date on which the institution began operations.

Title: Established Date
Definition: The date on which the institution began operations.

Title: Interest Expense: Subordinated notes and debenture
Definition: Total interest expense on subordinated notes and debentures.

Title: Interest Expense:Demand notes, US treasury & other
Definition: Total interest expense on demand notes issued to the US Treasury, other borrowed money and interest on mortgage indebtedness and obligations under capitalized leases on a consolidated basis.

Title: Extraordinary gains, net
Definition: Extraordinary items and other adjustments, net of income taxes.

Title: FDIC Regions
Definition: The six geographic FDIC Regions and their respective states are: new york (02) – states: connecticut, delaware, maine, maryland, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Puerto Rico, Rhode Island, Vermont, Virgin Islands Atlanta (05) - States: Alabama, Florida, Georgia, North Carolina, South Carolina, Virginia Chicago (09)–States: Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, Ohio Kansas City (11) – States: Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota Dallas (13)- States: Arkansas, Colorado, Louisiana, Mississippi, New Mexico, Oklahoma, Tennessee, Texas San Francisco (14)–States: Alaska, American Samoa, Arizona, California, Federated States of Micronesia, Guam, Hawaii, Idaho, Montana, Nevada, Oregon, Utah, Washington, Wyoming

Title: FDIC Supervisory Region
Definition: The supervisory FDIC office assigned to the institution. The FDIC Supervisory Regions and their respective states are: new york (02) – states: connecticut, delaware, maine, maryland, massachusetts, new hampshire, new jersey, new York, Pennsylvania, Puerto Rico, Rhode Island, Vermont, Virgin Islands Atlanta (05) - States: Alabama, Florida, Georgia, North Carolina, South Carolina, Virginia Chicago (09)–States: Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, Ohio Kansas City (11) – States: Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, South Dakota Dallas (13)- States: Arkansas, Colorado, Louisiana, Mississippi, New Mexico, Oklahoma, Tennessee, Texas San Francisco (14)–States: Alaska, American Samoa, Arizona, California, Federated States of Micronesia, Guam, Hawaii, Idaho, Montana, Nevada, Oregon, Utah, Washington, Wyoming Washington Office (15) - Division of Risk Management Supervision (RMS) Washington Office (16)– The Office of Complex Financial Institutions (CFI)

Title: Federal Reserve District
Definition: The Federal Reserve District in which the institution is physically located.

Title: FDIC Field Office
Definition: The FDIC Field Office where an institution is physically located.

Title: Federal funds sold and reverse repurchase
Definition: Total federal funds sold and securities purchased under agreements to resell in domestic offices.  Includes only federal Funds sold for TRF Reporters before March 1998.

Title: Federal funds purchased and repurchase agreements
Definition: Total federal funds purchased and securities sold under agreements to repurchase in domestic offices. Thrift Financial Reports include only federal funds purchased.

Title: Foreign exchange rate contracts
Definition: Notional amount of all foreign exchange contracts.

Title: Commitments to purchase foreign currencies & U.S. dollar exchange
Definition: Futures and forward foreign exchange contract commitments (gross amounts).  The gross amount of contracts committing the reporting institution to purchase foreign currencies and U.S. dollar exchange, whose predominant risk characteristic is foreign exchange risk.

Title: Notional value of exchange swaps
Definition: The notional principal amount (in U.S. dollars) of all cross-currency interest rate swaps.  The notional amount of a cross-currency interest rate swap is generally the underlying principal amount upon which the exchange is based.  A cross-currency interest rate swap is a transaction in which two parties agree to exchange principal amounts of different currencies (usually at the prevailing spot rate) at the inception of an agreement, which lasts for a certain number of years.

Title: Purchased option contracts
Definition: The contract amount of option contracts where the reporting bank has, for a fee, purchased the right to either purchase or sell an equity instrument, equity index, a commodity, or product not reportable as an interest rate or foreign exchange contract.
